# Cloudflare Pages response headers for FlowTyping — WAVE 1 (deliberately minimal).
#
# These are HTTP *response* headers, re-applied by CF at the edge on every
# response from this file. Change the file, redeploy, and the next response
# carries the new value — nothing here is durably cached by the browser.
#
# Only zero-lock-in, non-breaking headers live here on purpose. The two heavy
# headers are DEFERRED to a focused security-headers wave — see
# docs/deploy/security-headers.md (full rationale, ready CSP draft, HSTS ladder):
#   • Content-Security-Policy — powerful, but the single header most likely to
#     block legitimate loads (e.g. the Convex WebSocket). Deserves its own pass:
#     build + verify connect-src on a preview URL, decide kit.csp hash-mode and
#     self-hosted fonts alongside P0-4.
#   • Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS) — the ONE genuinely sticky header: the
#     browser remembers it for max-age (and 'preload' bakes into browser
#     binaries; both are slow/hard to undo). CF Pages already redirects
#     HTTP→HTTPS at the edge, so launch loses little without it.
#
# Docs: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
